cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of selecting a set of measurements from sensor observations to minimize error in estimating a parameter vector. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes the use of random matrix theory, which is a common tool in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.NA, and cs.MM.
